gov.nih.nlm.meme.xml
Class Version

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.meme.xml.Version
public class Version
extends Object

History:

08/15/2005:
Better handling of wrapper classes. This will help support jdk1.5.
06/17/2005:
Updated javadoc comments.
01/25/2005:
MedlineHandler only prints "PMID not found" messages for records that are not being ignored. ObjectXMLSerializer updated to serialize Properties and Hashtable objects correctly. Formatting was standardized and javadocs were checked.
01/25/2005:
MASRequestSerializer now supports "reconnect requests". It has a copy method for turning one request into another. MedlineHandler uses patterns for massaging poorly formatted dates. Data comes from meme_properties ObjectXMLSerializer does a better job with fields that used to be there.
12/13/2004:
ObjectXMLSerializer has more sophisticated mechanism for tracking primitives.
11/03/2004:
Minor documentation changes. MedlineHandler updated to handle new dates found in the MEDLINE info.
07/09/2004:
MedlineHandler handles additional bad dates in the PubDate field of the medline XML docs.
03/17/2004:
ObjectXMLSerializer bug fix to handle special characters in Var tags. Also the serializer now handles java.sql.Date and no longer treats NativeIdentifier as a primitive.
02/06/2004:
MASRequestSerializer handles SAXExceptions better. ObjectXMLSerializer was overhauled to more consistently deal with classes we want to treat as primitives. We also added support for treating native identifiers as primitives. A great deal of redundant (or useless) code was removed.
01/20/2004:
MedlineHandler employs a more aggressive algorithm for matching MSH main heading string in the Medline files.
11/07/2003:
ObjectXMLSerializer will not allow a field of a class called "id" to be set by the id attribute in an Object tag (same for idref, name, and length). This is a bug fix.
08/26/2003:
MedlineHandler supports UTF-8. ObjectXMLSerializer ignores the perThreadBuffer variable of the java 1.4.2 Integer class for parsing.
08/01/2003:
ObjectXMLSerializer was updated to deal with a problem in serializing exceptions having to do with not being able to find valid constructors for interface types.
06/19/2003:
MedlineHandler has still more additional improperly formatted date handlers.
06/06/2003:
MedlineHandler handles additional improperly formatted dates. MEMEServiceRequest now tracks the writer from the socket, allowing services to directly write their own responses. CGIStyleMEMEServiceRequest supports multiple CGI parameters with the same name (as a String[] parameter).
05/21/2003:
ObjectXMLSerializer reports better details when throwing reflection exceptions.
05/16/2003:
ObjectXMLSerializer was updated to report better exceptions when classes cannot be instantiated.
05/09/2003:
ObjectXMLSerializer now deals with '\r'. CGIStyleMEMEServiceRequest supports multiple CGI params with the same name (important for graphing application).
04/10/2003:
ObjectXMLSerializer now properly handles tab characters within attributes by converting them to .
04/01/2003:
ObjectXMLSerializer was updated slightly to provide better error messages. MASRequestSerializer clears the ObjectXMLSerializer data structures between the Server and Client sections of the document. This is necessary because there are two distinct <Object> documents within the <MASRequest> document itself. CGIStyleMEMEServiceRequest was given get/set methods to provide direct access to the requests socket output stream. This allows cgi sytle requests to directly return binary data, like images.
03/19/2003:
ObjectXMLSerializer made more efficient by expanding what is treated as "primtive", since primitives are written out as tag attributes instead of sub-Object tags. We now consider a certain set of common objects to be primitive as well as all idrefs.
11/13/2002:
Small changes to the MedlineHandler to deal with the NLM vs NLM-MED problem. Also, we discovered a problem with respect to synchronizing actions to the MRD. The operations_queue table contains XML fragments that may have CDATA sections within. These document fragments are placed within larger XML documents (in CDATA sections) if an action is fully read and then transported via the MEMEServiceRequest mechanism. I believe this problem can be worked around with the use of XMLEntityEncoder on the inner block with CDATA fragments.
08/28/2002:
The MASRequestSerializer and ObjectXMLSerializer were upgraded to support SAX parsing instead of DOM parsing. This version also brings with it the addition of MedlineHandler.

Author:
MEME Group
